itions and mineral context for the Strecker step if kept as a surface reaction."]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_003": 0.38, "rxn_006": 0.68, "rxn_008": 0.86}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.64, "pathway_coherence": 0.74, "environmental_progression": 0.79, "target_achievement": 0.88, "overall_confidence": 0.7, "feedback": "This route benefits from using the shared cyanide hub, but it inherits two major weaknesses: speculative generation of HCN/formamide from formaldehyde and ammonia, and the under-demonstrated 2-hydroxybutanal Strecker step. It is topologically valid but only modestly supported chemically and by literature.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_003", "rxn_006"], "suggestions": ["Use spark-discharge or other literature-supported HCN generation instead of rxn_003.", "Add direct support or explicit caveat for the hydroxybutanal precursor branch.", "Improve precursor provenance for mol_010."]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_009": 0.42}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.42, "pathway_coherence": 0.58, "environmental_progression": 0.5, "target_achievement": 0.6, "overall_confidence": 0.48, "feedback": "This is one of the weakest branches. The network treats glycine plus acetaldehyde as a one-step route to threonine/allothreonine, but the literature only supports this as a plausible historical proposal, not a validated direct prebiotic threonine synthesis. Mechanistically this likely requires multiple steps, activation, and poor selectivity, none of which are represented.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_009"], "suggestions": ["Expand this into explicit aldol/iminium or related intermediate chemistry rather than a single direct conversion.", "Treat as speculative unless a stronger source is available.", "Include side products and lower target confidence."]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_011": 0.78}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.79, "pathway_coherence": 0.86, "environmental_progression": 0.7