nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Threonine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network centers threonine formation around the two best-supported direct abiotic routes in the supplied literature: (i) aminomalononitrile (AMN) reactions with electrophiles followed by hydrolysis, and (ii) spark-discharge/Miller-Urey production of complex precursor pools that yield threonine and allothreonine after aqueous workup. Additional literature-retained branches are included as hypothesis-level or precursor-level routes only where necessary to create a complete connected bipartite network, and are explicitly marked as speculative where the report says direct threonine-specific evidence is lacking. Hydrothermal chemistry is used mainly to generate simple feedstocks and environmental constraints, while surface environments host cyanide, aldehyde, and sugar concentration chemistry, and biochemical/prebiotic settings perform final hydrolysis, assembly, and concentration. The network also incorporates hydrothermal destruction constraints for threonine, consistent with the report.\n\nMOLECULES (20 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH3N (methanimine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CHN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_009: C2H4N2 (aminomalononitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C4H8O2 (2-hydroxybutanal) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H8N2O (threonine aminonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H8O4 (threose) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: CH4 (methane) [starting]\n  - mol_015: N2 (nitrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_016: H2O (water) [starting]\n  