ic routes, the retained evidence consistently supports **mixtures involving threonine and allothreonine**, rather than selective formation of a single stereoisomer. No validated upstream artifact provided a recoverable numeric **threo/allo ratio**.\n\nA major unresolved gap is quantitative: the final yield artifact explicitly documents that **no verified numeric threonine yield was recovered for any retained route** using the available workspace and source-access tooling. Therefore, the ranked route table below contains **no yield-backed numeric rows**; all routes are retained and explicitly marked as **yield not recoverable / not reported in available validated extraction**.\n\n## 2. Ranked route table\n**Ranking rule required by task:** yield-backed routes first, flagged. **Result from validated upstream artifacts:** no retained route has a recoverable numeric yield. Therefore, there are **0 yield-backed routes** and all retained routes appear below as non-yield rows, with yield fields carried unaltered from upstream.\n\n| Rank group | Route ID | Yield-backed flag | Route name | Precursors | Route type | T | P | pH | Catalyst / agents | Phase / medium | Environment | Threo/allo selectivity | Yield | Citation | Exact locator |\n|---|---:|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Non-yield | R1 | NO | Strecker / 2-hydroxybutanal | 2-hydroxybutanal + NH3 + HCN + H2O | Strecker / 2-hydroxybutanal | not reported / not recovered | not reported / not recovered | pH-sensitive carbonyl/imine/aminonitrile equilibria; exact numeric pH not extracted | NH3, CN- / HCN | aqueous; hydrolysis workup required | cyanide-bearing surface waters / evaporative ponds | mixed threo/allo predicted; no direct measured ratio retrieved | yield/data not recoverable - source access unavailable (source: R1; reference: threonine_hypotheses.md citing Magrino et al. 2021 J Phys Chem Lett and Strecker-related source-list entries) | threonine_hypotheses.md citing Magrino et al. 2021